SIMPLE: outlook
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outlook
<hw>Out*look"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
face down; to outstare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>outlook</qex> conquest, and to win renown.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inspect thoroughly; to select.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outlook</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outlook
<hw>Out"look`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of looking
out; watch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who looks out; also, the place from which one
looks out; a watchtower.</def> <rj><au>Lyon Playfair.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The view obtained by one looking out; scope of
vision; sight; appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Applause⟦br⟧
Which owes to man's short <qex>outlook</qex> all its charms.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The likely outcome, such as is indicated by the
present situation; prospects; prognosis; <as>as, the <ex>outlook</ex> is
grim</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The point of view or attitude of a person; <as>as,
one's <ex>outlook</ex> on life is affected by illness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outloose</ent>⟦br⟧
